@kevingame3198  disagree with that. I concede that that's the official reason, but it isn't as if F4 readership dropped because fans SAW that film, let alone were put off the comic because of it. 

Since the film flopped, though, Fox was less likely to spend another hundred million dollars on a second reboot. Disney could bury the first family in the comics, devaluing the franchise and allowing them to scoop it up at a discount. 
Of course, they just swooped up the entire company, but I'm willing to bet that strategy was bandied about.

@Otto81 I could have overlooked all the flaws in Endgame if they would have simply made the “final battle scene” epic, worthy, and exciting. it it was such a let down and pathetic. 

The only reason why people proclaim Endgame was amazing is because they are so emotionally and financially invested in the MCU that it can’t fail in their own minds. 

Endgame was trash.

@SeSeReRfRf Most of the early MCU success came from Jon Favreau & Joss Whedon, plus a bunch of other experienced producers/ film makers like Kenneth Brannagh ( Thor 1) or Gale Anne Hurd ( James Cameron´s ex wife, producer of Terminator 1 & 2, Aliens, Abyss, first 2 Seasons of TWD and many other movies), who worked on the Edward Norton Hulk. 
Favreau was the one who pushed for RDJ as Tony Stark, despite the fact that the studio didn´t wanted him & Whedon pretty much laid down the entire story-arc leading up to the first "Avengers" movie.
The Russos came on board during "Phase 2", when the MCU was already established.

